replies.body:
Thanks for your points and meh, English is my second language but I understand your points overall. It is quite an issue with player's toxicity as sometimes, even though its just a "video game", I really sometimes feel negative about myself. Your points are quite true as I can notice myself changed - as in my behavior and attitude from the video game that I love to play. I sometimes be angry for no reason or with minor problems and get very sensitive to depression and anger management. 

However, if I reflect back to what I did when I play the game, I also to be toxic when someone misunderstood my statement and does a mistake. Also, retaliate from a toxic statement from team mates - I cannot stand people making fun about my mum.{{item:3751}} 
It is this weird thing, you know that is bad for the community and you know how it affects people but you still do it?!
